Deputy governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), Mr Adebayo Adelabu, has resigned his appointment with the bank after his letter of resignation to President Muhammadu Buhari was received and approved. His resignation takes effect from July 15, 2018. Adelabu was in charge of operations at the CBN. Reason for his resignation was not made known to journalists. Acting director, corporate communications department of the central bank in a statement yesterday said President Buhari has formally accepted the disengagement of the deputy governor. In a letter dated May 24, 2018 , and personally signed by him, President Buhari thanked Adelabu for his services to the country and wished him the best in his future ambitions. “While appreciating your services in the Central Bank of Nigeria since April 9, 2014, I wish you the very best in your future ambitions and continued commitment to public service in our country and specifically, as you seek to play a more active role in politics, in your home State,” the letter stated, according to Okorafor. Adelabu formally assumed duty as deputy governor at the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) on April 9, 2014, and served at different times as deputy governor in charge of Financial System Stability (FSS), Corporate Services (CS), and lastly Operations (Ops), before he tendered his letter of disengement from service.